This paper discusses the use of differential privacy in the context of a counting query, which is a common problem in database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of Bayesian estimation to improve the accuracy of the query, which is related to topics in cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-off between privacy and accuracy, which is related to topics in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
